# SCRUM-<n>: <short summary of what changed>
#
# Why this change (the motivation, not a paraphrase of the diff):
#
#
# Optional Smart Commit commands (processed by the GitHub-for-Jira app):
#   #comment <text>            — adds a comment to the issue
#   #time 1h 30m <text>        — logs work
#   #to-do | #in-progress |    — transitions the issue (developer intent)
#   #in-review | #done
#
# Examples:
#   SCRUM-12 #in-progress wiring carrier-of-record into requireVerifiedCarrier
#   SCRUM-45 #done #time 2h #comment FMCSA stub added for staging
#
# Multiple issues in one commit are fine:
#   SCRUM-12 SCRUM-45 deploy: staging release
#
# Note: Smart Commits require the GitHub-for-Jira app installed on the Jira
# site and your commit-email linked to your Atlassian account. See
# docs/jira-smart-commits.md for setup details.
